
## Running the Application

1. Ensure you have set the `GOOGLE_API_KEY` environment variable
2. Build the project:
   ```bash
   ./gradlew build
   ```
3. Run the application:
   ```bash
   GOOGLE_API_KEY=<YOUR_API_KEY> ./gradlew run
   ```

## Getting a Google API Key

To obtain a Google API key for Gemini:

1. Go to the [Google AI Studio](https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
2. Create or sign in to your Google Cloud account
3. Create a new API key
4. Copy the API key and set it as your environment variable as shown above

## Security Notes

- Keep your API key secure and never share it
- Consider using a `.env` file for local development (remember to add it to `.gitignore`)
- For production environments, use secure secret management systems
